source: An entity field containing an entity reference to a specific revision.

An entity reference can be displayed as a simple label with or without a link to the entity. Alternatively, the referenced entity can be displayed as a teaser (or any other available view mode) inside the referencing entity.

source: Delete orphaned composite entities revisions that are no longer referenced. If there are no revisions left, the entity will be deleted as long as it is not used.
Delete revisions of entities that are no longer used in Entity Reference Revisions fields.

Depending on the chosen entity type, additional filtering and sorting options are available for the list of entities that can be referred to, in the field settings. For example, the list of users can be filtered by role and sorted by name or ID.

Select the field(s) that will be searched when using the autocomplete widget.
Selects referenceable entities for an entity reference revisions field.

The %target_bundle bundle (entity type: %target_entity_type) was deleted. As a result, the %field_name entity reference revisions field (entity_type: %entity_type, bundle: %bundle) no longer specifies a specific target bundle. The field will now accept any bundle and may need to be adjusted.
The settings and the display of the entity reference field can be configured separately. See the Field UI help for more information on how to manage fields and their display.
target: Le impostazioni e la visualizzazione del campo entity reference possono essere configurati separatamente. Leggere l'aiuto di Field UI per ulteriori informazioni su come gestire i campi e la loro visualizzazione.

source: The Entity Reference Revisions module allows you to create fields that contain links to other entities (such as content items, taxonomy terms, etc.) within the site. This allows you, for example, to include a link to a user within a content item. For more information, see the online documentation for the Entity Reference Revisions module and the Field module help page.
The submission of the current form can cause the deletion of entities that are still used, backup all data first.
